Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.59,0:01:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:63593,66963}{\i1}May 1871.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.96,0:01:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:66963,70567}{\i1}At the time when Paris was\Nexpecting an attack from Prussia,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.56,0:01:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:70567,77707}{\i1}Thiers was already putting in motion his plan\Nthat used the French troops at Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.70,0:01:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:77707,81645}{\i1}The capital of France was\Nbetween a rock and a hard place.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.84,0:01:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:82846,90153}{\i1}The people of Paris\Ncontinued to call for battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.15,0:01:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:90153,94791}{\i1}encouraging each other to try to break\Nthrough the army besieging their city.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.79,0:01:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:94791,100530}{\i1}Their enthusiasm was slowly\Nrubbing off even on foreigners.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.53,0:01:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:102532,105268}The troops of these Versailles\Nhypocrites are already close.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.26,0:01:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:105268,108038}We must raise barricades.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.03,0:01:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:108038,110040}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.97,0:01:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:112976,116780}Jules, I will help you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.78,0:01:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:116780,118882}No, you should sit and rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.88,0:02:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:118882,122319}I'll be alright.\NA little effort won't hurt me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.15,0:02:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:124154,128258}Geneviève, don't give me\Nmore to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.25,0:02:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:128258,130927}You know that you have\Nto take it easy now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.42,0:02:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:131428,132329}But…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.49,0:02:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:132495,134598}Please, don't argue with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.70,0:02:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:136700,138101}Maybe I can give you a hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.36,0:02:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:139369,140437}Victor?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.77,0:02:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:140770,141805}Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.57,0:02:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:142572,145108}Jules, let me help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.57,0:02:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:147577,150447}I don't mean just you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.44,0:02:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:150447,154217}Exactly.\NWe will help you defend this city.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.41,0:02:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:154417,155552}Andréa?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.55,0:02:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:155552,159723}Yes. We're all back,\Nready to defend our capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.35,0:02:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:161358,162626}Isabelle!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.62,0:02:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:162626,164127}Sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.49,0:02:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:164494,167030}Ah, Isabelle!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.03,0:02:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:167030,168598}How have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.59,0:02:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:168598,170567}I was about to ask you the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.20,0:02:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:171201,174337}There is no time\Nto get emotional.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.33,0:02:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:174337,176640}Our enemies will\Nbe here any minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.17,0:03:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:179175,181011}Citizens of Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.01,0:03:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:181011,183913}We will soon launch an attack\Non Paris and I am sure
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.91,0:03:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:183913,188051}that we'll be able to reclaim both the city\Nand our wealth from these scum.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.39,0:03:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:193390,195625}Ladies and gentlemen,\Nthis moment has come.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.62,0:03:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:195625,198895}The moment when we will regain\Neverything that belongs to us!
