Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.53,0:04:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:274537,279576}{\i1}The Rostains' mansion in Paris was still\Nstanding, as if nothing had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.24,0:04:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:280243,284380}{\i1}It was the place where Isabelle was born\Nand raised without any worries.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.31,0:04:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:285315,287283}I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.28,0:04:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:287283,289385}I'm back here…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.01,0:05:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:290019,301931}{\i1}Something was definitely missing:\Nthe laugh of her father Léon and mother Marie.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.75,0:05:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:327757,329225}Isabelle?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.29,0:05:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:332295,334297}Sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.29,0:05:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:334297,338268}I remember our father sitting there\Nand listening to you playing the piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.80,0:05:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:338802,341204}And there is Mom's chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.03,0:05:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:343039,346843}After the fact,\NI think they died because of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.52,0:05:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:357520,358488}It's your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.98,0:06:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:359989,363359}You killed Marie.\NYou ruined the Rostain family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.63,0:06:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:371634,376172}Yes. We destroyed our family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.17,0:06:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:376172,378608}However, I do not intend\Nto regret anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.34,0:06:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:379342,384113}You don't regret anything?\NHow can you be so strong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.11,0:06:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:384113,386082}It's all thanks to Jules.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.08,0:06:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:386082,388017}It's thanks to my love for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.25,0:06:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:388251,391287}He is currently building a new Paris.\NOne that the world has never seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.32,0:06:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:393323,396459}I'm not that rich, naive\NGeneviève anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.29,0:06:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:398294,400129}I am a Parisian now,\None of many.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.12,0:06:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:400129,403766}We will create a city where\Nthe poor will have something to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.76,0:06:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:403766,407103}Stop. You're only\Nfooling yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.10,0:06:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:407103,409305}Yes. Perhaps you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.30,0:06:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:409305,413643}Isabelle,\NI am carrying Jules' child.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.64,0:06:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:413643,415311}What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.25,0:07:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:422252,426256}The fruit of our love.\NA new life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.25,0:07:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:426256,430927}Soon, this child will be walking\Nthe streets of this city.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.16,0:07:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:432161,434464}I hope it is so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.46,0:07:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:434464,437634}All the more reason for you to run!\NAll hell will break loose here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.63,0:07:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:437634,442705}I want to protect the city\Nthat our children will live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.70,0:07:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:442705,445341}Don't you get that you can die?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.34,0:07:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:445341,450580}If you die… If you die, what\Ndo you think happens to the child?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.78,0:07:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:450780,452849}If that happens,\Nthat's the God's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.84,0:07:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:452849,456386}Our child will understand\Nthis in Heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.38,0:07:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:456386,459088}Ah, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.08,0:07:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:459088,462058}How about, like,\Nasking their opinion first?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.05,0:07:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:462058,465228}What is it about this city\Nthat you all want to die for it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.26,0:07:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:466262,466896}Isabelle…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.13,0:07:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:468131,470500}Why did you come back here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.23,0:07:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:471234,472669}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.27,0:07:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:475271,478942}{\i1}Actually, that's a good question…\NWhy did I come back?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.24,0:08:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:480243,482578}Certainly not because of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.68,0:08:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:483680,485782}{\i1}Isabelle…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.78,0:08:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:485782,488584}{\i1}I don't know what\Nthe future holds.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.58,0:08:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:488584,492588}{\i1}But I want to believe\Nin Jules. I really do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.39,0:08:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:497393,501197}These points will be the most\Neffective positions for barricades.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.79,0:08:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:501798,505535}But in order to win, we must accept\Nthat we may have to abandon them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.53,0:08:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:505535,508805}There is always a chance that\Nthe enemy will come from behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.80,0:08:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:508805,511541}Sometimes you have to lose a battle\Nto win the war. That is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.54,0:08:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:511541,516913}That's all nice, Victor, but you need soldiers\Nwho can execute orders without complaints.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.24,0:08:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:517246,520783}Unfortunately, we all know that our people\Nhave never held weapons in their hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.08,0:08:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:521084,524554}Well, since there's no other option,\Nwe don't have much choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.55,0:08:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:524554,525888}Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.22,0:08:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:526222,529425}Okay, Andréa. You will take\Ncommand of the first barricade.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.42,0:08:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:529425,530326}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.32,0:08:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:530326,532662}Jules, you over the second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.82,0:08:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:532829,535064}Blanchard,\Nyou'll command the third.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.96,0:08:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:535965,539836}With this map, we could suppress\Nthe rebellion in a single day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.93,0:09:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:540937,542905}Well, well, what kind\Nof voyeur is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.74,0:09:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:544741,546242}Damn…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.64,0:09:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:547643,550346}I think that if we can hold these points,\Nwe stand a good chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.34,0:09:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:550346,551014}Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.01,0:09:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:551014,553082}Panza?!\NWhat are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.44,0:09:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:553449,556652}Do you realize that this room\Nwas originally occupied by Mr. Thiers?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.65,0:09:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:556652,559322}There are many devices hidden here\Nthat you have no idea about.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.32,0:09:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:559322,562759}But who would've thought that\NCount Red was Andréa all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.75,0:09:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:562759,566863}You were supposed to die in the Battle\Nof Champigny. How did you survive?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.03,0:09:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:567030,570533}Don't yammer so much. I'd like to\Nremind you that you're at our mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.83,0:09:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:570833,572602}At your mercy? Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.60,0:09:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:572602,574270}Do you really see it this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.27,0:09:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:574270,575872}Up against the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.27,0:09:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:579275,580777}Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.51,0:09:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:581511,584414}It appears that\Nthe tables have turned.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.41,0:09:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:584414,587483}If you value this girl's life,\Nyou'll bring me the map.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.65,0:09:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:594657,596993}Bring me the map.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.32,0:10:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:597326,600063}You scum.\NI won't forgive you this, Panza!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.03,0:10:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:602031,603199}Don't do that, my love.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.19,0:10:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:603199,604834}Your life is priceless to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.43,0:10:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:609439,610239}My love…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.94,0:10:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:616946,618414}Andréa.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.81,0:10:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:618815,619682}Irma!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.51,0:10:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:620516,622718}All right, boys!\NTear them apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.75,0:10:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:623753,625354}Irma! Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.62,0:10:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:627623,629158}I wanted to.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.15,0:10:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:629158,632095}I won't let anyone\Nget in your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.66,0:10:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:633663,636566}I am truly happy that we met.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.96,0:10:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:638968,641204}Irma… Irma!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.07,0:10:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:646075,647176}This rat…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.49,0:11:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:667497,668931}Die!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.70,0:11:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:677707,679108}Irma!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.94,0:11:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:680943,682145}Irma…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.84,0:11:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:686849,688317}Andréa.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.52,0:11:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:695525,699996}Victor, do you know… Do you know\Nwhat dirt and grass smell like?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.89,0:11:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:700897,703166}Irma was a wonderful woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.03,0:11:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:704033,709605}She taught me the smell\Nof dirt and grass.
Comment: 0,0:11:58.81,0:11:58.81,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:718814,718814}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.54,0:12:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:719549,724353}Ladies and gentlemen, the time\Nto launch the attack is fast approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.35,0:12:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:724353,729058}We must eliminate the villains\Nwho occupy our Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.05,0:12:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:729058,732161}They are devils\Ndisguised as French.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.16,0:12:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:732161,735498}Even in the skin of a woman or a child,\Ndevil's nature remains the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.49,0:12:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:735498,738167}We must erase Satan\Nfrom our world!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.16,0:12:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:738167,740102}Kill everyone without exception!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.10,0:12:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:740102,741337}Kill!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.33,0:12:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:741337,742505}Kill!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.50,0:12:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:742505,743739}Kill!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.73,0:12:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:743739,745007}Kill!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.00,0:12:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:745007,746342}Kill!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.34,0:12:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:746342,747710}Kill!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.71,0:12:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:747710,748711}Kill!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.71,0:12:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:748711,749745}Kill!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.74,0:12:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:749745,750913}Kill!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.62,0:12:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:758621,760756}Think you're\Naiming at the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.95,0:12:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:760957,764760}If you don't shoot first,\Nthey'll do it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.76,0:12:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:764760,766462}Then you will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.46,0:12:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:766462,768364}Remember this\Nand do not hesitate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.36,0:12:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:768364,773869}You keep talking about this enemy,\Nbut they're Frenchmen like us, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.86,0:13:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:773869,780443}That's right They're ordinary people who\Ndidn't do anything to me. Why kill them?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.44,0:13:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:780443,782378}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.98,0:13:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:784981,785848}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.08,0:13:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:787083,787850}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.55,0:13:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:793556,795591}These people\Nwouldn't even kill a fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.59,0:13:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:795591,798261}Good Lord.\NWhat are our chances?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.59,0:13:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:799595,801797}What matters is that\Nwe cannot afford a failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.49,0:13:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:803499,807737}A perfect city, ruled by its citizens.\NThis is the dream of many of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.73,0:13:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:807737,812341}But what does it look like\Nin reality? Can we build this city?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.34,0:13:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:812341,814910}Indeed, I want to defend Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.91,0:13:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:814910,817346}I want to stand up\Nfor what I believe is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.34,0:13:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:817346,819448}I know that many Parisians\Nshare my feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.44,0:13:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:819448,822485}However, feelings alone\Ndon't change anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.48,0:13:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:822485,826756}The army that will come here\Ncouldn't care less about feelings!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.75,0:13:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:826756,831594}Sooner or later, the morale\Nof the people of Paris will break.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.09,0:13:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:832094,837099}Exactly. None of us have\Na clue about politics or war.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.09,0:14:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:837099,840102}However imperfect it would be,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.10,0:14:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:840102,845107}the idea of a city governed by the people,\Nfor the people was born here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.10,0:14:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:845107,847376}We must show that it is doable.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.01,0:14:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:848010,851847}I understand all this.\NBut how? How?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.84,0:14:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:851847,853849}We can't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.31,0:14:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:854317,856752}So you are leaving Paris?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.05,0:14:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:857053,860623}No. If that was the case, I wouldn't\Nhave come here all the way from London.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.62,0:14:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:860623,864293}I will stay with the citizens\Nof this city to the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.20,0:14:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:877206,880976}Geneviève, do you really believe\Nthat we can make a change?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.77,0:14:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:882778,885581}Jules, where do\Nthese doubts come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.58,0:14:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:885581,890686}{\fscx95}You don't believe in the voice of our people,\Nthe voice that is crying as we speak?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.89,0:14:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:896892,899295}We will defend our city!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.46,0:15:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:899462,903899}If not us, then who? It's time to\Ntake matters into your own hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.26,0:15:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:904266,906102}This is it! Defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.10,0:15:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:906102,908137}Sounds good!\NThis is our city!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.13,0:15:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:908137,909271}Defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.27,0:15:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:909271,912441}Praise Paris!\NPraise Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.41,0:15:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:914410,916946}Defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.08,0:15:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:920082,923285}Just listen to this.\NThis is our voice. The voice of our hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.28,0:15:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:923285,925721}Our city is being built anew.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.72,0:15:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:925721,929058}A new city, by the people,\Nfor the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.13,0:15:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:941137,943372}Yes. Their voice is\Nthe voice of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.03,0:15:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:944039,948778}Remember that we must bring this\Nto an end also for the sake of our child.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.77,0:15:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:948778,951247}Yes, of course, you are right.\NNonetheless…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.24,0:15:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:951247,954984}Come on, stop worrying so much.\NTomorrow is Sunday.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.98,0:15:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:954984,958053}How about we celebrate\Nthe birth of our new city?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.05,0:16:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:958053,961624}You are a Parisian.\NYou still like to have fun, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.62,0:16:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:961624,963292}Geneviève…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.70,0:16:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:976705,984313}{\i1}Sunday, May 21, 1871.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.08,0:16:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:985080,988317}{\i1}It was a sunny day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.21,0:16:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:990219,994924}{\i1}The citizens of Paris\Nhave decided to celebrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.92,0:16:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:994924,998761}{\i1}Dance parties took place\Non the streets around the entire city.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.82,0:16:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:999829,1004200}{\i1}For the first time in a long time,\Npeople relaxed a little
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.20,0:16:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1004200,1008237}{\i1}and they sang,\Ndrank and danced.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.00,0:16:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1010005,1014176}Excuse me, gentlemen, would be one of you\Nwilling to dance with my daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.48,0:17:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1023486,1026088}{\i1}Irma, today, we're celebrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.45,0:17:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1026455,1028958}{\i1}Everyone is having fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.38,0:17:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1055384,1058187}Come, Andréa,\Ncome dance with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.18,0:17:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1058187,1060022}You'll lighten up a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.02,0:17:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1060022,1062625}No "but"s.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.19,0:17:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1064193,1065561}I can finally congratulate you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.56,0:17:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1065561,1066529}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.52,0:17:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1066529,1069265}I'm happy for you.\NCan you still dance?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.26,0:17:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1069265,1071000}Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.51,0:18:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1082511,1087149}They look so enchanting.\NAs if they were made for each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.14,0:18:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1087149,1089919}Isabelle, let's go, too.\NCome on, let's dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.91,0:18:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1089919,1090519}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.51,0:18:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1090519,1092688}What are you two sitting for\Non such a beautiful day?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.68,0:18:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1092688,1094523}Jules! Let me dance with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.52,0:18:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1094523,1095858}I'm sorry, Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.29,0:18:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1097293,1101864}I'm slowly getting used to the notion\Nthat it'll always look like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.87,0:18:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1107870,1108704}My lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.70,0:18:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1108704,1110839}Really? With me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.72,0:18:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1129725,1137032}{\i1}That Sunday was the last one that\Nthe citizens of Paris could blithely enjoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.94,0:19:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1151947,1153983}Everyone, take cover!\NAndréa, follow me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.01,0:19:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1157019,1157753}Victor…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.35,0:19:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1158354,1160723}Victor! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.72,0:19:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1160723,1162491}Isabelle!\NWhere are you going?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.76,0:19:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1167763,1169098}Save yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.03,0:19:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1171033,1176605}{\i1}The Versailles army has\Nfinally launched the attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.04,0:19:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1179041,1186949}{\i1}For the trained army of Versailles,\Nthe citizens of Paris were not a challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.59,0:20:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1198594,1200195}Everyone at once! Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.73,0:20:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1208737,1210439}Okay! We're backing away!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.83,0:20:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1210839,1212374}Backing away? No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.70,0:20:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1212708,1213642}Excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.64,0:20:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1213642,1217546}This is our district.\NWe grew up here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.54,0:20:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1217546,1219915}We're not going anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.91,0:20:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1219915,1223452}Fools! That wasn't the plan!\NRetreat immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.98,0:20:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1226989,1230592}If I have to die anyway, I'd rather do it here.\NI want to go down near my house!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.59,0:20:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1230592,1233262}Exactly. This is our place.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.26,0:20:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1233262,1235330}We can't just give it up to them!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.33,0:20:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1235330,1236932}Long live Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.93,0:20:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1236932,1238934}Long live our city!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.63,0:20:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1240636,1242204}Together—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.13,0:20:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1244139,1246608}We will defend our…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.68,0:20:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1254683,1259321}{\i1}The citizens of Paris\Ndidn't know when to withdraw.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.02,0:21:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1260022,1262057}{\i1}Familiar side streets.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.05,0:21:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1262057,1263659}{\i1}Cobblestone stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.65,0:21:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1263659,1266962}{\i1}The walls they doodled on\Nwhen they were young.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.96,0:21:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1266962,1269932}{\i1}Finally, their own homes.\NThey just wanted to protect these.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.93,0:21:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1269932,1273535}{\i1}One after another, they fell dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.26,0:21:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1274269,1278474}{\i1}This is not a fight. It's a massacre.\NA massacre of the Paris people.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.41,0:21:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1285414,1289151}I didn't know… I didn't know\Nthat it was so important to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.15,0:21:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1289151,1290953}Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.62,0:21:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1291620,1293655}Isabelle!\NWhat are you doing here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.62,0:21:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1294623,1296024}Follow me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.45,0:21:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1297459,1298994}We're getting out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.76,0:21:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1305768,1307102}Victor…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.17,0:21:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1309171,1310405}Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.97,0:21:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1311974,1313008}Victor…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.21,0:21:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1316211,1317746}Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.25,0:22:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1323252,1324753}G… Geneviève?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.95,0:22:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1328957,1330425}Is that you, Geneviève?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.09,0:22:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1332094,1333729}Yes. It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.36,0:22:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1336365,1338600}G… Geneviève…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.43,0:22:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1340435,1342538}I am here with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.53,0:22:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1342538,1343605}Victor…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.84,0:22:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1352848,1354082}Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.08,0:22:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1354082,1355350}Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.31,0:22:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1356318,1358220}Victor…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.25,0:22:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1363258,1365727}Victor…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.77,0:22:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1378774,1379474}Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.47,0:23:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1379474,1380442}Isabelle!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.44,0:23:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1380442,1382311}Isabelle!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.14,0:23:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1383145,1385314}Isabelle, we have to run!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.78,0:23:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1387783,1389451}Come on, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.81,0:23:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1390819,1392187}Victor…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.18,0:23:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1392187,1394256}Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.25,0:23:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1394256,1395958}Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.09,0:23:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1399094,1400662}Let me go, Jean!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.26,0:23:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1401263,1402931}Victor…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.93,0:23:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1402931,1404333}Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.86,0:23:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1404867,1407436}Victor!…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.64,0:23:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1412641,1416178}{\i1}That evening in Paris,\Na great fire broke out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.74,0:23:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1417746,1423619}{\i1}Flames escaping high into the sky crowned\Nthe suffering of the city's inhabitants.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.75,0:23:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1430759,1435464}Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.29,0:23:57.79,Credits,[credits],0,0,0,,{TIME:1433295,1437799}{\fad(200,0)\c&HFAFAFA&\blur1\fs17\an5\pos(527,362)}To be continued
